In the context of the fractional quantum Hall effect one encounters very
often particles which obey some exotic (anyonic) statistics. So far we have
assumed our particles to obey fermionic type statistics as this choice is
most natural for the investigated theories. However, one can
easily implement more general statistics by adding a matrix  to the 
-matrix.

