Conclusions 

We have presented two concrete applications in which  non-perturbative
methods developed in the context of integrable quantum field theories can be
used to evaluate physical quantities. We predict the generation of harmonic
spectra from solid state devices and show that filling fractions occurring
in fractional quantum Hall systems can be obtained from minimal affine Toda
field theories.

